HEADWORD: Manufacturing
<hw>Man`u*fac"tur*ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Employed, or
chiefly employed, in manufacture; <as>as, a <ex>manufacturing</ex>
community; a <ex>manufacturing</ex> town.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to manufacture; <as>as,
<ex>manufacturing</ex> projects</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>manufacturing business</ent>⟦br⟧
